{"article_id":"K92AI3EEcLB0hqyN","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"NEW YORK","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( ) -","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Front-runner Donald Trump showed signs","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"of tightening his grip on the Republican U.S. presidential nomination on Wednesday","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"when chief rival Ted Cruz acknowledged","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"his own only hope","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"of wresting control","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"is a contested convention .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump speaks at a campaign event at the Indiana State Fairgrounds in Indianapolis , Indiana","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"April 20 , 2016 .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"/Aaron P. Bernstein","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"Trump delivered a crushing defeat of Cruz in Tuesday ' s New York Republican nominating contest","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"while Democratic front-runner Hillary Clinton broke rival Bernie Sanders ' string of state victories with a definitive win of her own .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Rebounding from a defeat in Wisconsin two weeks ago ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Trump set himself up for another big night on April 26 ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"when the Northeast U.S. states of Pennsylvania , Connecticut , Rhode Island , Delaware , and Maryland hold primaries .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"\" Ted Cruz is mathematically out of winning the race , \"","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"Trump tweeted on Wednesday .","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"\" Now all","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"he can do","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"is be a spoiler ,","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"never a nice thing","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"to do .","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"I will beat Hillary ! \"","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Trump , 69 , predicted some \" amazing weeks \" ahead for his campaign .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Cruz , at a news conference on the sidelines of a Republican National Committee meeting in Hollywood , Florida , said","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"neither he nor Trump will amass the 1,237 delegates","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"needed to win the nomination","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"without a contested convention in Cleveland","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"starting on July 18 .","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"\" What is clear today is that we are headed toward a contested convention .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Nobody is able to reach 1,237 .","depth":15},{"id":32,"text":"I ' m not going to reach 1,237 ,","depth":16},{"id":33,"text":"and Donald Trump is not going to reach 1,237 , \"","depth":16},{"id":34,"text":"said Cruz , a U.S. senator from Texas .","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"New York boosted Trump ' s delegate tally to 845 ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"while Cruz has 559","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"and Kasich 147 ,","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"according to the Associated Press .","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"Next Tuesday ' s contests offer 172 delegates for Republicans .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"If Trump , a New York billionaire , and Clinton , a former U.S. secretary of state , go on to secure their respective parties ' nominations ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"a /Ipsos national opinion poll shows Clinton with a sizeable lead","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"if the Nov. 8 election were held today .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"In the latest poll of likely general election voters , 45 percent said","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"they would support Clinton","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"while 35 percent would support Trump","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"if the two were running against each other .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"The April 15-19 poll surveyed 1,334 people","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"and had a credibility interval of 3.1 percentage points .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"A former reality TV star , Trump has adopted a more measured tone in recent days","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"and appears to be trying to heal wounds","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"inflicted by a campaign","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that has alarmed many in the Republican establishment .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"He sent campaign advisers to the party meeting in Florida","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"that began on Wednesday .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"\" There ' s only two issues left for Republicans :","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Will Trump get 50 percent of the delegates prior to Cleveland ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"if not ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"how close will he be ?","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"New York gives him a nice boost ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"but it will take weeks","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"before we know the answer , \"","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"said Ari Fleischer ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"who was White House spokesman under President George W. Bush .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Cruz , 45 , came in third in New York .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Ohio Governor John Kasich , 63 , a long-shot candidate , sought to use his second-place showing in New York as proof","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"he is emerging as Trump ' s central challenger .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Trump won at least 89 delegates in New York ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"while Kasich got at least three ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"according to the AP .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Cruz did not win any ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"prompting Trump adviser Sarah Huckabee Sanders to urge him on CNN on Wednesday to \" get out of the way \"","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"once the math of delegate counts makes it impossible for him to prevail .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"The win by Clinton , 68 , makes it nearly impossible for Sanders , 74 , to overtake her commanding lead in delegates","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"needed to secure the nomination .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Clinton clinched at least 175 out of 291 New York delegates ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"while Sanders won at least 106 ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"according to the AP .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"A U.S. senator from Vermont , Sanders has vowed to fight until the Democrats ' nominating convention in Philadelphia","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"starting on July 25 .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Democratic strategist Jim Manley said","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Clinton has the delicate task","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"of trying to attract Sanders supporters","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"drawn to his leftist campaign promises ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"while switching focus to the task","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"of beating the eventual Republican nominee .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"\" She runs a risk .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"If she goes too far to the left","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"she ' s going to upset independents and others","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that she ' s going to need in the general , \"","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Manley said .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":183,"left":0,"right":182,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":182,"left":1,"right":181,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":181,"left":100,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":97,"right":99,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":93,"right":96,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":4,"right":95,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":95,"left":94,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":94,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":137,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":128,"right":136,"relation":"ela